            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1295295989,
            "creation_date": 1295295989,
            "body": "<p>You need to change it to:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public static void LaunchMinecraft()\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>That way, the static <code>Main<\/code> method can access the static <code>LaunchMinecraft<\/code> method.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 4717524,
            "question_id": 4717498
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/c5ca0194c4cfd38e4531ef115e9d5167?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 2871,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 4068,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4068/austin-salonen",
                "reputation": 50401,
                "display_name": "Austin Salonen",
                "accept_rate": 89
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 4,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1295296128,
            "creation_date": 1295296128,
            "body": "<p><code>LaunchMinecraft<\/code> is not a static method so you cannot access it in the static method <code>Main<\/code> without calling it from the <code>Program<\/code> object.<\/p>\n\n<p>Two options<br>\n 1. Make <code>LaunchMinecraft<\/code> static  <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public void LaunchMinecraft() \n{ ... }  \n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>2. Create a new <code>Program<\/code> object in <code>Main<\/code> and call it that way.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>var program = new Program();\nprogram.LaunchMinecraft();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 4717542,
            "question_id": 4717498
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/33d1848da81c469e3f19bd7e1d8919d9?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
                "account_id": 43462,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 127059,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/127059/femaref",
                "reputation": 61509,
                "display_name": "Femaref",
                "accept_rate": 90
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 2.5",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1295295952,
            "creation_date": 1295295952,
            "body": "<p>You are trying to call an instance method (ie. a method that needs a specific object to operate on) from a static method (a method that works without a specific object). Make the <code>LaunchMinecraft<\/code> method static as well.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 4717518,
            "question_id": 4717498
        },
        {
            "owner": {
